      "date": "2023-03-17 03:57:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Can you explain what %private at the end means?  Just at the end of\n > the commit title or ?\n\nThis is explained in the Gerrit documentation:\nhttps://review.whamcloud.com/Documentation/user-upload.html#_git_push\n\n  Private Changes\n\n  To push a private change or to turn a change private on push\n  the private option can be specified:\n\n  git push ssh://john.doe@git.example.com:29418/kernel/common HEAD:refs/for/master%private\n\n  Omitting the private option when pushing updates to a private\n  change doesn’t make change non-private again. To remove the\n  private flag from a change on push, explicitly specify the\n  remove-private option:\n\n  git push ssh://john.doe@git.example.com:29418/kernel/common HEAD:refs/for/master%remove-private",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
